description: From Latin sextuplicātus, past participle form of sextuplicāre (“to sextuple”), from sextuplus (“sixfold”), from sextus (“sixth”) (from sex (“six”)) + -plus (“-fold”) (from plicare (“to fold”)).

entries.meaning: Six times the number, volume, length, etc. (of something else).
examples: The customer ordered a sextuplicate quantity.

entries.meaning: A series, set, collection, or group of six identical copies of something.
examples: If the official receipt is not available, the appropriate CA officer will prepare a similar receipt in sextuplicate.

verbs.description: sextuplicate (third-person singular simple present sextuplicates, present participle sextuplicating, simple past and past participle sextuplicated)

examples: Sextuplicate this document for me, please.
